<subSubSection id="C34CD692D10B496B79C3C0DEFDAE359A" pageId="18" pageNumber="75" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BE98519D10B496B79C3C0DEFEBF35CD" blockId="18.[189,324,401,427]" box="[189,324,401,427]" pageId="18" pageNumber="75">
<heading id="D0A13275D10B496B79C3C0DEFEBF35CD" bold="true" box="[189,324,401,427]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="18" pageNumber="75" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B922590BD10B496B79C3C0DEFEBF35CD" bold="true" box="[189,324,401,427]" pageId="18" pageNumber="75">Etymology</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE98519D10B496B79C3C0F0FDAE359A" blockId="18.[188,1398,447,509]" pageId="18" pageNumber="75">
The specific epithet refers to its similarity with the extant species 
<taxonomicName id="4C56FE9AD10B496B7ACEC0F0FA8D35BC" authority="(Thomson, 1858)" authorityName="" baseAuthorityName="Thomson" baseAuthorityYear="1858" box="[944,1398,447,474]" class="Insecta" family="Diapriidae" genus="Pantolyta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="75" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="macrocera">
<emphasis id="B922590BD10B496B7ACEC0F0FB5D35BF" box="[944,1190,447,473]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="75">Pantolyta macrocera</emphasis>
(Thomson, 1858)
</taxonomicName>
and is to be treated as an adjective.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C34CD692D10B496B79C3C36BFBC536BB" pageId="18" pageNumber="75" type="materials_examined">
